
 * it is not a server, it is a framework,

 * it uses even driven programming,

 * it simplifies network programming, TCP and UDP socket servers,

 * it uses the reactor pattern of programming,

 worth to know:

 * every operation is returned right after the call,
 - operation object is waiting for the data that will fill that object,

 implementation:

 *  Netty has its own ChannelFuture interface.
 We can pass a callback to ChannelFuture which will be called upon operation completion.

 use cases:

 * high performance protocol servers,